quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  7,96,"And if the people of the towns believed and feared Allah, We would have opened for them blessings from the heavens and the earth, but they disbelieved. So, We seized them for what they used to earn for themselves."
  7,97,"So, do the people of the towns feel secure from Our punishment coming upon them at night while they are asleep?"
  7,98,"And do the people of the towns feel secure from Our punishment coming upon them in broad daylight while they are at play?"
  7,99,"So, do they feel secure from the plan of Allah? So, no one feels secure from the plan of Allah but the people who are losers."
  7,100,"Is it not a guidance to those who inherit the land after it's ( former) inhabitants that, if We so will, We would afflict, them for their sins? And We seal their hearts so that they do not listen."
  7,101,"Those are the towns We narrate to you of their important events. And surely their messengers came to them with clear signs, but they were not to believe in what they had belied earlier. This is how Allah seals the hearts of the disbelievers."
  7,102,"And We did not find with most of them any covenant (unbroken), and surely We have found most of them sinners."
  7,103,"Then after them We sent Musa with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs then , they did injustice to them. So, look, how was the fate of the mischief-makers."
  7,104,"And Musa said ,"O Pharaoh, I am a messenger from the Lord of the worlds,"